IntroductionGameStop Corp.  - Strategy and SWOT Report, is a source of comprehensive company data and information. The report covers the company’s structure, operation, SWOT analysis, product and service offerings and corporate actions, providing a 360? view of the company.Features: - Detailed information on GameStop Corp. required for business and competitor intelligence needs - A study of the major internal and external factors affecting GameStop Corp. in the form of a SWOT analysis - An in-depth view of the business model of GameStop Corp. including a breakdown and examination of key business segments - Intelligence on GameStop Corp.’s mergers and acquisitions (M&A), strategic partnerships and alliances, capital raising, private equity transactions, and financial and legal advisors - News about GameStop Corp., such as business expansion, restructuring, and contract wins - Large number of easy-to-grasp charts and graphs that present important data and key trendsHighlights:GameStop Corp. (GameStop or 'the company') is a specialty retailer of video game hardware and software, as well as new and pre-owned mobile and consumer electronics products. The company operates in the US, Canada, Australia and Europe. It is headquartered in Grapevine, Texas and employed about 18,000 full-time employees as of January 31, 2015.  The company recorded revenues of $9,296 million during the financial year ended January 2015 (FY2015), an increase of 2.8% over FY2014. The operating profit of the company was $618.3 million in FY2015, an increase of 7.8% over FY2014. The net profit of the company was $393.1 million in FY2015, an increase of 11% over FY2014.Reasons to Purchase: - Gain understanding of GameStop Corp. and the factors that influence its strategies  - Track strategic initiatives of the company and latest corporate news and actions  - Assess GameStop Corp. as a prospective partner, vendor or supplier - Support sales activities by understanding your customers' businesses better - Stay up to date on GameStop Corp.’s business structure, strategy and prospects
	

